    "description": "Are you a skilled Curriculum Developer looking for your next big career move? Amity University Advisory Limited in Mysuru offers you the perfect platform to grow professionally and personally.\n\nAbout Amity University Advisory Limited:\nAmity University Advisory Limited is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Utilize technology and digital tools to enhance learning outcomes\n• Participate in teacher training and professional development programs\n• Maintain student records and prepare progress reports\n• Monitor student progress and provide timely feedback\n• Collaborate with faculty on curriculum development initiatives\n• Develop and deliver engaging lesson plans for students\n• Participate in school events, workshops, and training programs\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBBS / MD / MS from recognized medical college\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Data Analysis\n• Proficiency in Student Assessment\n• Proficiency in LMS Platforms\n• Proficiency in Communication Skills\n• Proficiency in Classroom Management\n• Proficiency in Lesson Planning\n• Proficiency in IB Curriculum\n• Proficiency in Bloom's Taxonomy\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Mysuru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Amity University Advisory Limited!",
